Heat oil in a saucepan over medium heat. Add onions and garlic; saute about 5 minutes, or until onions are translucent. Add paprika and cook 1 minute. Add cider and bay leaves; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes. Add chorizo and sun-dried tomatoes; simmer an additional 5 minutes. Remove bay leaves. Sprinkle with parsley. Serve hot with hearty bread to dip in sauce.